rComments: Shes a great professor, does her part to ensure lectures are interesting, genuinely cares about her students, and is extremely accessible outside of class. Highly recommend!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Explains well, her quizzes were easy enough if you practiced before and was always ready to help at her office hours. I liked her a lot! The final was hard though.

She teaches alright. Her quizzes are a bit difficult than other professors so I do advise you to sit into various ADM2350 professors. She is clear in her expectations so you won't be tooooo* surprised with the quiz content. Definitely study all past quizzes and finals to do well in her class.

Many people found her to be mean, but she's just very sarcastic. If you go to class and pay attention, you should get a decent grade. Exams and tests reflect what you do in class. I bought the textbook and didn't use it, her slides were good.

Really good prof. Going to be unbiased even though I think she's the best prof I've had. Very lecture heavy, 4 quizzes, not hard to grasp the content if you just go to class and listen. Slides give you all the information you need. I didn't buy the textbook and had a fine time. If you get her as a prof and go to the classes, you'll get an A.
